        <body>
            <p rend="Newspaper clipping:">INTERESTING MOVEMENT AMONG JEWS.—<lb/> From the
                    <placeName>south of Russia</placeName>, where there are<lb/> thousands of Jews
                dwelling in almost every<lb/> town (according to a statistical note lately<lb/>
                published, there are nearly two millions of<lb/> Jews residing in the
                    <placeName>Russian Empire</placeName>), we<lb/> have received letters of
                heart-thrilling inter-<lb/>est, telling us of a most wonderful move-<lb/>ment going
                on silently among the Jews in-<lb/>habiting that portion of this country. Some<lb/>
                of them are actually longing and begging<lb/> for missionaries and teachers to be
                sent out<lb/> to explain to them the Scriptures. They<lb/> are thirsting for the
                living waters of the<lb/> Word; for they are without the necessary<lb/> books and
                Scriptures to go on searching by<lb/> themselves; for in one place about thirty<lb/>
                Jews secretly meet together to read the New<lb/> Testament—[Macedonian,</p>
            <p rend="Body of letter:"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I enclosed above<lb/> extract, taken from one of our<lb/> papers
                here. You may have<lb/> seen it before.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your <add>?</add></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">J N Cardoza</persName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>St Paul</placeName>
                <date>15 Jany/66</date>
            </p>
        </body>
